d of bison at this spot, as well as a measure of Folsom's pivotal role in American archaeology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAnimal remains (Archaeology)zNew MexicozColfax County. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zNew MexicozColfax County. 0aFolsom culturezNew MexicozColfax County. 0aFolsom pointszNew MexicozColfax County. 0aFolsom points. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aamerican archaeology.  aantiquity.  aarchaeology.  aartifacts.  abedrock.  abison.  abonebed.  acarcasses.  aenvironment.  afieldwork.  afolsom.  ageochronology.  ageology.  ahistory.  ahunters.  ahunting.  aice age.  aland use.  alate glacial period.  amuseum.  anew mexico.  anew world.  apaleoecology.  apaleoindian hunters.  apaleoindian.  apaleontology.  apaleotopography.  aprehistoric.  aprehistory.  ascience.  asocial science.  aspear points.  avillage.1 aBalakrishnan, Meena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolliday, Vance T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Bonnie F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott-Cummings, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTheler, James L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTodd, Lawrence C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWinkler, Alisa J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093244940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932449/original  a978-3-11-0